thread.title_full: Girls basketball: Cambridge holds off Lake Mills 39-35 to win home opener - NewsBreak

author: Daily Jefferson County Union
title: Girls basketball: Cambridge holds off Lake Mills 39-35 to win home opener - NewsBreak
text:
10 hours ago
CAMBRIDGE â€” Junior guard Tara Bettenhausen scored 12 points, junior wing Macy Robinson added 10 as Cambridge edged out visiting Lake Mills 39-35 in nonconference girls basketball on Tuesday.
Senior wing Finley Tuscic added seven points and freshman guard Mya Robinson contributed six for the Blue Jays (1-1), who outscored the L-Cats (1-2) 17-13 in the second half.
Junior guard Milan Fullerton led Lake Mills with 12 points, all of which came in the first half. Sophomore guard Sydney Grundahl scored her nine points in the second half and sophomore guard Hannah Kulow added seven points.
"It was a competitive game," Lake Mills girls basketball coach Vivian Guerrero said. "These early games in the season are a good test and let us know what we need to work on to get ready for conference.
"I was proud of how hard our girls fought and adjusted mid game. These girls have so much room to grow and we are excited to get back after it."
Cambridge hosts Madison Abundant Life on Monday while Lake Mills plays at Whitewater next Tuesday.
